---
title: Veggie Lo Mein with Mushrooms, Green Beans, and Ginger Soy Sauce
description: If you’ve never had udon, you’re in for a treat. It’s a thick and delightfully chewy Japanese noodle similar to our beloved spaghetti. In this dish, we dress it up in style with a hefty dose of colorful veggies and three knockout flavors: sweet hoisin, salty soy, and fragrant ginger.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/veggie-lo-mein-118f5c53.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/veggie-lo-mein-7c0291cb.pdf
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 501 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 75 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 15 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1332 mg
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/veggie-lo-mein-w35-5797b58a16a86635298b4568
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Remove the @udon noodles{8%ounce} from the refrigerator
to come to room temperature. Trim the ends of the @green beans{6%ounce}, then cut
into 1-inch pieces. Peel and mince the @ginger{1%thumb}. Mince or grate the
@garlic{2%cloves}. Peel the @carrots{1}. Cut in half lengthwise, then slice into
thin half moons. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites
separate. Thinly slice the @button mushrooms{4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add the mushrooms, carrot, and green beans. Cook, tossing, for ~{5-7%minutes},
until softened and slightly golden brown. Add the ginger, scallion whites,
garlic, and another drizzle of olive oil (if needed). Cook, tossing, another
~{1%minute}, until fragrant. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @soy sauce{4.5%teaspoon}, @veggie stock
concentrate{1}, @hoisin sauce jar{1%jar}, @honey{1%teaspoon}, and ¼ cup water.
Stir to combine.

Add the sauce to the pan and reduce until thickened, about ~{1%minute}. Add the
udon noodles to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until they are
tender. If the pan becomes too dry, add a splash of water or drizzle of olive
oil. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve: Divide the veggie lo mein between bowls and garnish with the
scallion greens and @cashew pieces{1%ounce}. Enjoy!